This paper deals with text simplification and machine translation, which are both sub-fields of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses deep neural networks for translation, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the neural network, which is related to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions knowledge distillation, which is a technique used in neural networks and falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of automatic translations, which is related to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
